Reasoning: The paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of a PTAS (polynomial-time approximation scheme) suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The consideration of energy consumption and speed-scaling cost suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of weighted completion time and generalized global cost functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
